                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Linux Mint Debian Edition 7 Just Got Its First Beta Release]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-mint-debian-edition-7-just-got-its-first-beta-release/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/linux-mint-logo-on-a-default-background.jpg" length="36" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux Mint]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            With a shiny new Debian 13 codebase.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Linux Mint just announced the beta release for LMDE 7, codenamed "Gigi." The beta release is available now, and you can download it from a variety of mirrors around the world. One of the more interesting things about this beta is that the root account is locked by default.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:34:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-mint-debian-edition-7-just-got-its-first-beta-release/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Add a User to a Group (or Second Group) on Linux]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/50787/add-a-user-to-a-group-or-second-group-on-linux/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chris Hoffman]]></dc:creator><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/52971068232_4f35bed8e9_o.jpg" length="180" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Files]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ubuntu]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Groups are a handy way to help keep permissions and ownership organized.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Changing the group a user is associated to is a fairly easy task, but not everybody knows the commands, especially to add a user to a secondary group. We'll walk through all the scenarios for you.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:15:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/50787/add-a-user-to-a-group-or-second-group-on-linux/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Chrome's Gemini Revamp Has Me Worried]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-chrome-revamp-has-me-worried/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/chrome2.jpg" length="127" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Chrome]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Gemini]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Finally, a web browser that tells me to eat glue and rocks.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google Chrome has slowly accumulated more generative AI features over the last two years, and now even more of them are on the way. Google has announced deeper integration with its Gemini AI assistant, including an “agent browsing assistant” that will attempt to automate online tasks.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-chrome-revamp-has-me-worried/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Use These Smart Home Routines Every Day, Here's Why]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-use-these-smart-home-routines-every-day-heres-why/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/a7309341.jpg" length="318" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[automation]]></category><category><![CDATA[HomePod mini]]></category><category><![CDATA[Voice Assistants]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I can't imagine life without them.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Are you intimidated by setting up smart home routines? I’ve gone down the rabbit hole and set up quite a few around my house. Some are complex, and some do just one thing. Here are my favorite smart home automations and how I use them.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-use-these-smart-home-routines-every-day-heres-why/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Make Sure You Never Miss an HTG Article: Set Us As a Preferred Source on Google]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/make-sure-you-never-miss-an-htg-article-set-us-as-a-preferred-source-on-google/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/phone-screen-showing-google-s-new-preferred-sources-feature-with-a-magnifying-glass-highlighting-the-feature-icon-2.png" length="1093" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[web browsers]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Want more How-To Geek? Customize your search results with our non-stop coverage. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>These days, the internet and the web are... complicated. Things are constantly changing, <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/google-search-results-are-getting-worse-heres-how-i-navigate-now/" target="_blank">search results are getting worse</a>, and the rise of AI tools, summaries, and algorithms makes it harder to get the content you actually want. Luckily, Google Search <a href="https://blog.google/products/search/preferred-sources/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">recently released</a> a new feature that puts you in control. You can finally set your own preferred sources and see the sites you want, like How-To Geek, more frequently.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 16:23:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/make-sure-you-never-miss-an-htg-article-set-us-as-a-preferred-source-on-google/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[What Is an RGB Mini-LED TV, and How Does It Compare to OLED?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/what-is-an-rgb-mini-led-tv-and-how-does-it-compare-to-oled/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gaurav Shukla]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/rgb-mini-led-hisense.jpg" length="1345" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hisense]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sony]]></category><category><![CDATA[TCL]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The battle for TV supremacy is heating up.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>After years of trying to compete with OLED TVs using enhancements like full-array local dimming, Mini-LEDs, and quantum dots, LED TV technology is ready to make a significant jump with the new RGB Mini-LED TVs.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/what-is-an-rgb-mini-led-tv-and-how-does-it-compare-to-oled/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Forgotten Luxury Sedan Still Turns Heads Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/forgotten-luxury-sedan-still-turns-heads-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2021-jaguar-xf-p300-r-dynamic-se-3.jpg" length="224" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sedans]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It’s still got the swagger, comfort, and charm that made it stand out—only now it feels even more like a hidden treasure.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/category/automotive/" target="_blank">Luxury sedans</a> come and go, but some deserve more credit than they get. The Jaguar XF is one of those cars—sleek, stylish, and quietly overlooked in a market that’s always chasing the next big thing.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 15:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/forgotten-luxury-sedan-still-turns-heads-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Intel and NVIDIA Will Make x86 Hardware]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/intel-and-nvidia-will-make-x86-hardware/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/the-nvidia-and-intel-logos-next-to-each-other-on-a-black-background.jpg" length="52" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nvidia]]></category><category><![CDATA[intel]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            NVIDIA is also taking a stake in Intel.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>NVIDIA and Intel have announced a historic collaboration that will see them jointly develop a new generation of custom processors for both data centers and personal computers. NVIDIA is also investing $5 billion in Intel's common stock.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 15:05:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/intel-and-nvidia-will-make-x86-hardware/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Made These 8 Custom Themes to Show What's Possible in macOS Tahoe]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/macos-26-tahoe-looks-youve-got-to-try-out/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/microsoft-bliss-in-macos-26.jpg" length="3442" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[customization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Customization is Bliss.jpg.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>With macOS 26, Apple is adding a whole heap of new customization tools to your Mac just as it did with the iPhone last year. You can now change your app icon styles, colors, accents, and combine them with all the old mainstays like dark or light mode and custom wallpapers.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 15:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/macos-26-tahoe-looks-youve-got-to-try-out/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Nothing's New Ear (3) Earbuds Are Truly Bizarre]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/nothing-new-ear-3-earbuds-are-truly-bizarre/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1000673890.jpg" length="174" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nothing]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Mics everywhere.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Nothing is most known for its smartphones these days, but the young company first started out as an audio company with an eventual goal of launching a phone. And just like its phones, its earbuds have gotten better. The latest earbuds by Nothing are here, and they're good—and weird.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 14:50:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/nothing-new-ear-3-earbuds-are-truly-bizarre/</guid></item></channel>
